# Acme Solo · Claude Code Operating Manual

> Drop-in operating manual for Acme Solo (1-person company · audience-services niche).
> Auto-loaded every session. Edit only on real shifts (every 1-2 months).

---

## 1 · You (the operator)

- **Role**: solo founder running Acme Solo · client-services + 1 self-built SaaS
- **Coding level**: 5+ years backend · just rewriting the React frontend after 3 years away · Claude Code is a force multiplier · architecture decisions need tradeoffs explicit
- **Workspace**: Claude Code (deep terminal · 6-8h/day) + Cursor (in-IDE quick edits)
- **Company stage**: post-PMF on services side · 2 paid SaaS pilots running · stage = scale services / find SaaS PMF
- **Communication**: English-leaning · client comms in English · internal notes mixed
- **Code conventions**: comments in English · variable names English · file names kebab-case

## 2 · Resources & boundaries

- Runway: 9 months at current burn (without new client revenue) · 14 months if services hold
- Customer channels: existing podcast (3.2k weekly) · 4 referral partners · LinkedIn DMs (~10 inbound/week)
- Legal entity: LLC (US single-member · pass-through tax)
- API budget: $200/month max · alerts at $150 via daily /cost check

## 3 · Collaboration rules

1. **Understand before doing**: vague request → ask 1-2 sharp questions · don't guess
2. **Brevity over flourish**: no over-engineering · no decorative comments · no irrelevant error handling
3. **Spell out tradeoffs**: tech proposals must call out main tradeoff (time / cost / maintainability)
4. **Cost-aware**: routine = Haiku · main task = Sonnet · strategy = Opus
5. **Major decisions**: architecture · tech debt · client commitments → log to `docs/decisions/YYYYMMDD-<slug>.md`
6. **Don't suggest revenue plays unsolicited** · but when asked · be direct

## 4 · Task routing

### Product line
| Task | Tool |
|---|---|
| Long session feature (>1h) · scripts · terminal | Claude Code main thread |
| In-IDE CSS / small fn / autocomplete | Cursor |
| Idea evaluation (build or skip) | skill: `idea-eval` |
| Feature / product implementation plan | `@planner` |
| Code review (pre-merge / pre-release) | `@code-reviewer` |
| Pre-release full audit | skill: `ship-checklist` |
| Batch content production | skill: `content-blitz` |

### Sales / revenue line
| Task | Tool |
|---|---|
| Discovery call script + lead scoring | skill: `lead-intake` |
| Interview → client proposal | skill: `proposal-gen` |
| Standard contract / SOW | template `docs/templates/SOW.md` |
| Post-delivery → 5 reusable content pieces | skill: `case-study-gen` |
| Pipeline status / follow-up cadence | `docs/pipeline.md` |
| Customer inquiries · post-sales · feedback | `@customer-support` |
| Outbound content | `@marketing` |

### Infra
- `docs/system-memory.md` — brand voice (warm-direct · no fluff) / pricing tiers ($5k/$12k/$25k for services) / lead weights / founder background
- `docs/handbook.md` — agent / skill triggers + walkthroughs
- `scripts/lib/` — reusable libs (lead-scorer.js · pipeline-tally.js)

### Session management
| Command | When to use |
|---|---|
| `/save-session` | Real handoffs only (project delivered · machine swap · ≥ 1 day gap) |
| `/resume-session` | New session after ≥ 1 day gap |
| `/learn` | Repeated correction or non-obvious confirmation |

**Rule**: Before `/save-session` ask "Will I look at this memo in 3 months?" Yes → save · No → skip.

## 5 · Multi-Claude collaboration

⚠️ Active concern · I run 2-3 sessions in parallel often (services + SaaS work).

### Mandatory startup scan (30s)
1. `CLAUDE.md` (auto)
2. `docs/contracts/*.md` — cross-module interface contracts
3. `docs/sessions/` latest 1-2 memos
4. SessionStart hook board (auto)

### Anti-patterns I've burned on
- ❌ Editing `lib/api-types.ts` from frontend session without checking backend contract → 4h debugging Saturday morning
- ❌ Two sessions starting dev servers on port 3000 → silent override → wrong data
- ❌ Modifying shared `docs/system-memory.md` without bumping version → next session uses stale weights

**Rule of thumb**: "Will another Claude pause for 1 second seeing my change?" Yes → contract / memo · No → just do it.

## 6 · Directory map

```
.claude/                — Claude Code config (this pack)
customers/              — One folder per client
products/               — saas-app/ (the SaaS pilot)
docs/
  ├── strategy.md
  ├── decisions/        — 14 ADRs to date
  ├── learnings/        — 23 entries
  ├── sessions/         — 8 handoff memos
  ├── contracts/        — 4 active contracts
  └── pipeline.md       — 6 active leads
```

## 7 · OSS-First product methodology

For any new product / direction:

1. Search GitHub for ≥1k-star projects in same domain — list 5-10 candidates
2. Run 1-2 with real data · 3 real cases · log startup time / output quality
3. Position your value layer: what's as-is / modified / they can't do
4. Fork + extend in outer layer · don't fork-and-rewrite

**Heuristic**: ≥1k-star same-domain repo? → fork+extend · No → caution (market may have died)

## 8 · API cost discipline

⚠️ Last quarter: $340 spent in one debugging weekend. Discipline:

Pattern: **dry-run shows cost estimate + full prompt → I review → explicit `--approve` flag → real call**.

When agents call paid APIs:
1. Run preview mode (no API call · only estimate)
2. Paste preview to chat
3. Wait for explicit "approve"
4. Only then add `--approve`

Banned: silently presetting `--approve` · "should be fine" hand-wave.

## 9 · State file decay discipline

⚠️ Burned by reading 2-month-old `docs/pipeline.md` and treating closed leads as open.

Rolling-state files mandatory:
1. Frontmatter must have `staleAfterDays` + `nextReviewBy`
2. AI reading expired rolling-state must proactively warn me
3. No TTL = invisible landmine

## 10 · Banned actions

- Don't write API keys / secrets / customer privacy into git-tracked files
- Without explicit approval: `rm -rf` · `git push --force` · prod DB changes · external email / social posting
- Estimate paid API cost before calling
- Never `--no-verify` / `--no-gpg-sign`

